    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "In this assignment we examine whether machine learning can be used to predict stock returns and generate economically meaningful investment strategies. The analysis is inspired by @10.1093/rfs/hhaa009 (henceforth GKX), who show using a broad set of machine learning models that non-linear methods outperform simple historical-mean benchmarks for cross-sectional return prediction. This stands in contrast to @10.1093/rfs/hhm014, who find that machine learning models generally fail to beat the historical mean for aggregate market return prediction. We attempt to replicate part of the GKX findings using their stock characteristics and macroeconomic predictors.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Data Preparation\n",
        "\n",
        "In this section we load and prepare the stock-level dataset for return prediction. The data are stored in a parquet file containing 94 stock characteristics from @10.1093/rfs/hhaa009 and 13 macroeconomic variables from @10.1093/rfs/hhm014, along with industry classifications, excess returns, and lagged market capitalizations."
      ],
      "id": "ac30b35a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "cache": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: ex1-load-and-filter\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Part (a): Load data and filter to post-2000 ──────────────────────────────\n",
        "# Relative path: resolves to the parquet file in the same folder as this .qmd\n",
        "df = pd.read_parquet(\"stock_characteristics_monthly.parquet\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Drop observations before January 2000 (data coverage and quality improve\n",
        "# substantially after this date, consistent with GKX sample construction)\n",
        "df = df[df[\"date\"] >= pd.Timestamp(\"2000-01-01\").date()].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Variable selection ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
        "# Stock characteristics (10): chosen based on consistently high variable\n",
        "# importance in GKX Table 4 / Figure 5 across all machine learning models.\n",
        "#   Momentum/Reversal (3): short-term reversal, 12-month and 36-month momentum\n",
        "#   Value            (2): book-to-market, earnings-to-price\n",
        "#   Size/Liquidity   (2): log market equity, dollar volume\n",
        "#   Profitability    (3): return on assets, gross profitability, investment-to-assets\n",
        "\n",
        "CHAR_COLS = [\n",
        "    \"characteristic_mom1m\",   # 1-month return (short-term reversal)\n",
        "    \"characteristic_mom12m\",  # 12-month price momentum\n",
        "    \"characteristic_mom36m\",  # 36-month long-term momentum\n",
        "    \"characteristic_bm\",      # Book-to-market ratio\n",
        "    \"characteristic_ep\",      # Earnings-to-price ratio\n",
        "    \"characteristic_mvel1\",   # Log market equity (size)\n",
        "    \"characteristic_dolvol\",  # Dollar trading volume (liquidity)\n",
        "    \"characteristic_roaq\",    # Return on assets (quarterly)\n",
        "    \"characteristic_gma\",     # Gross profitability (gross margin)\n",
        "    \"characteristic_invest\",  # Investment-to-assets ratio\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Macroeconomic predictors (4): selected from @10.1093/rfs/hhm014 based on\n",
        "# predictive power for the aggregate equity premium (GKX Table 4).\n",
        "#   dp  – dividend-price ratio (valuation level)\n",
        "#   ep  – earnings-price ratio (earnings yield)\n",
        "#   tbl – treasury-bill rate (level of short-term interest rates)\n",
        "#   tms – term spread (long minus short rate; business-cycle indicator)\n",
        "\n",
        "MACRO_COLS = [\n",
        "    \"macro_dp\",   # Dividend-price ratio\n",
        "    \"macro_ep\",   # Earnings-price ratio\n",
        "    \"macro_tbl\",  # Treasury-bill rate\n",
        "    \"macro_tms\",  # Term spread\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "ID_COLS = [\"permno\", \"date\", \"ret_excess\", \"mktcap_lag\", \"sic2\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Keep only selected columns\n",
        "data = df[ID_COLS + CHAR_COLS + MACRO_COLS].copy()"
      ],
