      "source": [
        "## Machine Learning Models\n",
        "\n",
        "We train two machine learning models to forecast monthly excess returns: a random forest and a neural network. Both are estimated within scikit-learn pipelines that include a standardisation step, ensuring that scale information from the validation and test sets does not leak into the preprocessing.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Random forest.** The objective is to minimize mean squared error (MSE) by averaging predictions from an ensemble of independently grown decision trees, each trained on a bootstrap sample of the data and a random subset of features at each split. The key hyperparameters are: the number of trees (`n_estimators`), the maximum tree depth (`max_depth`, which controls model complexity), and the minimum number of samples required in each leaf node (`min_samples_leaf`, which acts as a regulariser).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Neural network.** The objective is to minimise MSE via the Adam stochastic gradient descent algorithm. The architecture consists of fully connected layers with sigmoid activations. The key hyperparameters are: the hidden layer sizes (controlling depth and width), the L2 penalty coefficient (`alpha`, which regularises the weights), and the initial learning rate."
      ],
      "id": "a67bb20d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "cache": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: ex2-split\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Part (b): Time-respecting train / validation / test split ─────────────────\n",
        "# Split by unique calendar months to prevent any future information leaking into\n",
        "# training. The most recent 20% of months are held out as the test set (never\n",
        "# touched during model selection). The remaining 80% is split 75/25 into train\n",
        "# and validation, giving approximately 60% / 20% / 20% overall. A generous\n",
        "# training window captures multiple business cycles, while the validation set is\n",
        "# large enough for stable hyperparameter selection.\n",
        "\n",
        "unique_dates = np.sort(meta[\"date\"].unique())\n",
        "n_dates      = len(unique_dates)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Cutoff indices: TRAIN_FRAC of months for training, next 20% for validation, last 20% for testing\n",
        "test_cutoff = unique_dates[int(n_dates * VAL_FRAC)]\n",
        "val_cutoff  = unique_dates[int(n_dates * TRAIN_FRAC)]\n",
        "\n",
        "date_col = meta[\"date\"].values\n",
        "\n",
        "train_mask = date_col <  val_cutoff\n",
        "val_mask   = (date_col >= val_cutoff) & (date_col < test_cutoff)\n",
        "test_mask  = date_col >= test_cutoff\n",
        "\n",
        "# DataFrame versions for sklearn pipelines (preserve column names)\n",
        "X_train_df = X[train_mask].reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "X_val_df   = X[val_mask].reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "X_test_df  = X[test_mask].reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "y_train = y[train_mask]\n",
        "y_val   = y[val_mask]\n",
        "y_test  = y[test_mask]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Report date ranges for each split\n",
        "split_info = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    \"Set\":        [\"Training\", \"Validation\", \"Test\"],\n",
        "    \"Start date\": [\n",
        "        str(meta.loc[train_mask, \"date\"].min()),\n",
        "        str(meta.loc[val_mask,   \"date\"].min()),\n",
        "        str(meta.loc[test_mask,  \"date\"].min()),\n",
        "    ],\n",
        "    \"End date\": [\n",
        "        str(meta.loc[train_mask, \"date\"].max()),\n",
        "        str(meta.loc[val_mask,   \"date\"].max()),\n",
        "        str(meta.loc[test_mask,  \"date\"].max()),\n",
        "    ],\n",
        "    \"Observations\": [\n",
        "        f\"{train_mask.sum():,}\",\n",
        "        f\"{val_mask.sum():,}\",\n",
        "        f\"{test_mask.sum():,}\",\n",
        "    ],\n",
        "})\n",
        "display(Markdown(split_info.to_markdown(index=False)))"
      ],
      "id": "ex2-split",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "cache": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: ex2-preprocessor\n",
        "# ── Shared preprocessor ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
        "# StandardScaler is fit on the training set only and then applied to validation\n",
        "# and test sets. Tree-based models are scale-invariant, but including the scaler\n",
        "# keeps both pipelines consistent.\n",
        "continuous_cols = list(X.columns)\n",
        "\n",
        "preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(\n",
        "    transformers=[\n",
        "        (\"scale\", StandardScaler(), continuous_cols)\n",
        "    ],\n",
        "    remainder=\"drop\",\n",
        "    verbose_feature_names_out=False,\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "id": "ex2-preprocessor",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "cache": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: ex2-tune-rf\n",
        "#| fig-cap: Random forest validation MSE by maximum tree depth and minimum leaf size. Lower MSE indicates better out-of-sample fit on the validation period.\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Part (c): Random Forest – hyperparameter tuning ──────────────────────────\n",
        "_rf_model_path   = _dir / \"model_random_forest.joblib\"\n",
        "_rf_results_path = _dir / \"rf_tuning_results.joblib\"\n",
        "\n",
        "if _rf_model_path.exists() and _rf_results_path.exists():\n",
        "    # Load pre-trained model and tuning results from disk — skip re-tuning\n",
        "    best_rf        = joblib.load(_rf_model_path)\n",
        "    _rf_cache      = joblib.load(_rf_results_path)\n",
        "    rf_results_df  = _rf_cache[\"rf_results_df\"]\n",
        "    best_rf_params = _rf_cache[\"best_rf_params\"]\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    # Grid over max_depth (tree complexity) and min_samples_leaf (regularisation).\n",
        "    rf_grid = [\n",
        "        {\"regressor__n_estimators\":    N_ESTIMATORS_RF,\n",
        "         \"regressor__max_depth\":       d,\n",
        "         \"regressor__min_samples_leaf\": l}\n",
        "        for d in [10, 20]\n",
        "        for l in [20, 100]\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    rf_results = []\n",
        "    for params in rf_grid:\n",
        "        pipe = Pipeline([\n",
        "            (\"preprocessor\", preprocessor),\n",
        "            (\"regressor\", RandomForestRegressor(\n",
        "                n_estimators          = params[\"regressor__n_estimators\"],\n",
        "                max_depth             = params[\"regressor__max_depth\"],\n",
        "                min_samples_leaf      = params[\"regressor__min_samples_leaf\"],\n",
        "                n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "                random_state=RANDOM_STATE,\n",
        "            )),\n",
        "        ])\n",
        "        pipe.fit(X_train_df, y_train)\n",
        "        val_mse = mean_squared_error(y_val, pipe.predict(X_val_df))\n",
        "        rf_results.append({**params, \"val_mse\": val_mse})\n",
        "\n",
        "    rf_results_df  = pd.DataFrame(rf_results).sort_values(\"val_mse\")\n",
        "    best_rf_params = rf_results_df.iloc[0].drop(\"val_mse\").to_dict()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Refit best RF on training + validation combined for the final test predictions\n",
        "    best_rf = Pipeline([\n",
        "        (\"preprocessor\", preprocessor),\n",
        "        (\"regressor\", RandomForestRegressor(\n",
        "            n_estimators     = int(best_rf_params[\"regressor__n_estimators\"]),\n",
        "            max_depth        = int(best_rf_params[\"regressor__max_depth\"])\n",
        "                              if pd.notna(best_rf_params[\"regressor__max_depth\"]) else None,\n",
        "            min_samples_leaf = int(best_rf_params[\"regressor__min_samples_leaf\"]),\n",
        "            n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "            random_state=RANDOM_STATE,\n",
        "        )),\n",
        "    ])\n",
        "    best_rf.fit(\n",
        "        pd.concat([X_train_df, X_val_df], ignore_index=True),\n",
        "        np.concatenate([y_train, y_val]),\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
